14 TO REMEMBER PUBLIC SERVANT, PUBLIC
15 POLICY EXPERT, AND EMMY AWARD-WINNING
16 JOURNALIST ALICE STEWART.
17
18 WHEREAS, public servant, public policy expert, and Emmy-political
19 journalist Alice Stewart, formerly of Virginia, passed away May 18, 2024; and
20
21 WHEREAS, Alice Stewart was born March 11, 1966, in Atlanta, Georgia,
22 and started her career there as a local reporter and producer before moving
23 to Little Rock, Arkansas, in 1998 to be a news anchor with KARK-TV; and
24
25 WHEREAS, Alice Stewart went on to serve as the communications director
26 for then-Governor Michael Dale "Mike" Huckabee and also served in this role
27 for Huckabee during his presidential campaign in 2008; and
28
29 WHEREAS, Alice Stewart served the people of Arkansas as Deputy
30 Secretary of State under Arkansas Secretary of State Mark Martin; and
31
32 WHEREAS, Alice Stewart was communications director for the presidential
33 campaigns of former United States Representative Michele Bachmann, former
34 United States Senator Rick Santorum, and United States Senator Ted Cruz; and
35
36 WHEREAS, Alice Stewart was hired by CNN as a political commentator
