1 ahead of the 2016 presidential election and appeared on air frequently,
2 including as a regular guest of "The Situation Room with Wolf Blitzer"; and
3
4 WHEREAS, Alice Stewart also served on the senior advisory committee at
5 the Institute of Politics at Harvard University's Kennedy School, where she
6 previously was a fellow; and
7
8 WHEREAS, Alice Stewart was guided by a deep faith in Jesus Christ and a
9 strong conviction to follow Him, and was a faithful member of The Church at
10 Rock Creek in Little Rock, Arkansas; and
11
12 WHEREAS, Alice Stewart was devoted to loving her family well, and
13 adored her sisters Andrea Schwind and Heather Thompson (Pete), brother Eric
14 Fraker (Vikki), nieces Brittney Lerzo (Michael) and Katie Schwind, and
15 nephews Jonathan Schwind (Madison) and Thomas Schwind; and
16
17 WHEREAS, in her free time, Alice Stewart was an avid and competitive
18 runner, and was instrumental in the founding of the Little Rock Marathon,
19 serving in many roles, including Media Director; and
20
21 WHEREAS, Alice Stewart was a board member of Girls on the Run of
22 Central Arkansas, a nonprofit that honored her by saying of Alice Stewart,
23 "Alice knew the importance of teaching girls they have limitless potential
24 and the power inside to lift up themselves and others"; and
25
26 WHEREAS, Lieutenant Governor Leslie Rutledge said of Alice Stewart,
27 "Alice was a wonderful friend to me and never wavered in her love for others.
28 She was one of the hardest working people I have ever known. Alice was a
29 gracious and generous host, always inviting others to come fellowship with
30 her"; and
31
32 WHEREAS, CNN program host Wolf Blitzer said of Alice Stewart, "We
33 always invited her to come on my show because we knew we would be a little
34 bit smarter at the end of that conversation. She helped our viewers better
35 appreciate what was going on and that's why we will miss her so much"; and
